  "name": "Embodied Grammars: A Constellation",
  "description": "A map of maps. This meta grammar connects seven grammars of embodied knowledge — Yoga, Indian Classical Dance, Ballet, Modern Dance, Anthropological Dance, Theater, and Movement Culture. Each item here is a doorway into a full grammar. Together, they trace humanity's relationship to the moving body: as prayer, as protest, as play, as architecture, as liberation. The body is the first instrument; these are its many tunings.\n\nPUBLIC DOMAIN ILLUSTRATION REFERENCES: Eadweard Muybridge, *Animal Locomotion* (1887). Auguste Rodin, drawings of Cambodian dancers (1906). Henri Matisse, *La Danse* (1910). Nataraja bronze sculptures (Chola dynasty, 10th-12th century).",
  "grammar_type": "custom",
  "creator_name": "PlayfulProcess",
  "tags": ["embodiment", "dance", "yoga", "theater", "movement", "body", "constellation", "meta"],
  "roots": ["embodiment", "eastern-wisdom", "myth-and-symbol", "liberation"],
